    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "the design in Java was to turn ANY amount of strings into lists, which includes just 1 string (but also means there&#39;s only 1 way to do so). in other languages there are more than one way to do something, so i just wanted to know the best way (in this case, only 1 way), for example, ruby, you can say &quot;blah.first&quot; and &quot;blah.last&quot; as opposed to like &quot;blah[0]&quot;, which is very convenient and more readable. in Java, that doesn&#39;t seem to be the case. sorry, hope that made sense"
