      "post_id" : 29784337,
      "comment_id" : 69623950,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Ah, I see. Yes by default <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se7/html/jls-15.html#jls-15.12.2.5\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java will choose the most specific method</a>, which in this case is <code>Lists#newArrayList(Iterable&lt;? extends E&gt; elements)</code>. You can do <code>Lists.newArrayList(new Path[] {Paths.get(&quot;&#47;usr&#47;local&#47;this&#47;is&#47;not&#47;single&#47;‌​element&quot;)})</code> to explicitly call the vararg method, or just construct an empty list (<code>List&lt;Path&gt; p = Lists.newArrayList()</code>) and add the element (<code>p.add(Paths.get(&quot;&#47;usr&#47;local&#47;this&#47;is&#47;not&#47;single&#47;‌​element&quot;))</code>&zwnj;&#8203;)."
    } ],
