    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Yet another alternative is <a href=\"http://www.c2.com/cgi/wiki?DoubleBraceInitialization\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">double brace initialization</a>, e.g.</p>\n\n<pre><code>new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;() {{ add(s); }};\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>but <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/924285\">it is inefficient and obscure</a>. Therefore only suitable:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>in code that doesn't mind memory leaks, such as most unit tests and other short-lived programs;</li>\n<li>and if none of the other solutions apply, which I think implies you've scrolled all the way down here looking to populate a different type of container than the ArrayList in the question.</li>\n</ul>\n"
