  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/20358883/how-to-quickly-and-conveniently-create-a-one-element-arraylist",
  "closed_reason" : "Duplicate",
  "title" : "How to quickly and conveniently create a one element arraylist",
  "body" : "<p>Is there a Utility method somewhere that can do this in 1 line? I can't find it anywhere in <code>Collections</code>, or <code>List</code>.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public List&lt;String&gt; stringToOneElementList(String s) {\n    List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;String&gt;();\n    list.add(s);\n    return list;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>I don't want to re-invent the wheel unless I plan on putting fancy rims on it.</p>\n\n<p>Well... the type can be <code>T</code>, and not <code>String</code>. but you get the point. (with all the null checking, safety checks...etc)</p>\n"
